arcade.patch.agent.process

Class PatchProcessSignalingMedium

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.patch.agent.process.PatchProcess
      • arcade.patch.agent.process.PatchProcessSignaling
        • arcade.patch.agent.process.PatchProcessSignalingMedium
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Process

    public class PatchProcessSignalingMedium
extends PatchProcessSignaling
    Extension of PatchProcessSignaling for medium EGFR signaling.

    PatchProcessSignalingMedium represents a 8-component signaling network spanning the cytoplasm and cell membrane. Migratory flag is set based on fold change in active PLCg using MIGRATORY_THRESHOLD. Derived from PatchProcessSignalingComplex with simplified transcription and translation.

      • equations

        Solver.Equations equations
        System of ODEs for network.

        Uses three regulatory weights:

        • wG = increase in TGFa-EGFR phosphorylation by glucose
        • wP = increase in PLCg activation by p-TGFa-EGFR
        • wC = increase in TGFa-EGFR dephosphorylation by active PLCg

    • Constructor Detail

      • PatchProcessSignalingMedium

        public PatchProcessSignalingMedium(PatchCell cell)
        Creates a medium signaling Process for the given PatchCell.

        Initial concentrations of all components in the network are assigned and molecule names are added.

        Loaded parameters include:

        • MIGRATORY_THRESHOLD = threshold fold change in PLCg for migration
        Parameters:
        cell - the PatchCell the process is associated with
